            h6: "National Legal Framework: Royal Decree on Air Quality and Emissions sets pollutant limits and enforces industrial and urban monitoring. Regional regulations in Flanders, Wallonia, and Brussels-Capital govern emission standards for industries and vehicles. Environmental impact assessments are mandatory for projects likely to affect air quality. International Agreements & Obligations: Full compliance with EU Ambient Air Quality Directives, including PM2.5, PM10, NO2, ozone, and benzene standards. Participation in UNEP global air quality initiatives and reporting frameworks. Engagement with Convention on Long-Range Transboundary Air Pollution (CLRTAP) and Sustainable Development Goals targeting reduction of air pollution-related deaths."
